*************************************
* Additional Touchpad Configuration *
*************************************

All commands to type into terminal are written after $ sign.
Open up terminal and run following commands:

# Install libinput-gestures from AUR:
$ yay -S libinput-gestures

# Copy config file from /etc/libinput-gestures.conf into ~/.config:
$ sudo cp /etc/libinput-gestures.conf ~/.config

# Insert some useful touchpad gestures at the end of a file:

gesture swipe right 3 xdotool key Ctrl+Tab
gesture swipe left 3 xdotool key Ctrl+Alt+Tab
gesture pinch in 2 xdotool key Ctrl+minus
gesture pinch out 2 xdotool key Ctrl+plus

# Close and safe file
# Logout/Reboot

# Additional information can be found at:
# https://ethans.me/codes/optimize-touchpad-performance-on-linux-en_US
